A payment processing workflow uses an Activity that calls an external payment gateway. The Activity has a `start_to_close_timeout` of 30 seconds and a retry policy with `maximum_attempts: 3`. The Activity also heartbeats every 10 seconds with a `heartbeat_timeout` of 15 seconds. In production, a Worker completes the payment charge successfully but crashes before sending `ActivityTaskCompleted` to the Temporal Service. The payment gateway records the charge. On retry, the Activity uses `WorkflowRunID + ActivityID` as an idempotency key sent to the gateway. Which statement accurately describes the combined behavior of the retry mechanism, heartbeating, and idempotency key across this failure scenario?

```go
func (a *Activities) ChargePayment(ctx context.Context, req PaymentRequest) (PaymentResult, error) {
    key := fmt.Sprintf("%s-%s", activity.GetInfo(ctx).WorkflowExecution.RunID, activity.GetInfo(ctx).ActivityID)

    go func() {
        for {
            activity.RecordHeartbeat(ctx, nil)
            time.Sleep(10 * time.Second)
        }
    }()

    return a.gateway.Charge(ctx, req, key)
}
```
